title: Merge pull request #124 from fridayideas/analytics
message:
Merge pull request #124 from fridayideas/analytics

Since there's no nuget package for the analytics and the Xamarin component is way out of date, I've added the repo as a submodule reference to daytomato. This means that you'll either have to run `git submodule update --init` in your local copy or `git clone --recursive` when cloning. That, and make sure the .sln isn't open when you pull for this, because this pr modifies the solution file :)

Thanks, Alix!

title: Non-trivial GPS and maps restructuring.
message:
Non-trivial GPS and maps restructuring.

Things that have changed:
1. Instead of waiting (and possibly timing out) for the initial GPS location, everything subscribes asynchronously to the location change event. This makes working with the emulator less of a chore and prevents blocking on initial view load.

2. The clustering code in MapFragment has been overhauled to completely solve the jankiness problem. Before, every call to _map.AddPolygon(..) would block the main thread for an extraordinary amount of time (presumably due to some JNI shenanigans or such). Since we only ever use the resulting polygons as "bags of vertices", moving everything into the C# layer GREATLY reduces the amount of time spent on the main thread and essentially eliminates all of the jank and screen freezes that plagued earlier builds.

TODO:
- The trips and home view have not been refactored to use the new Location Change flow, and thus may report inaccurate results. Next steps are to find some balance between the push and pull-based API's in Geolocation and abstracting that into a service.

title: reduce jank on map pins load
message:
reduce jank on map pins load

Grabbing pins beforehand and moving the (somewhat expensive) clustering operation outside of the pin creation loop seems to alleviate some of the problems with view freezes when 100+ pins are loaded. Much work remains to be done in trying to reduce the cost of the pin merging procedure and proper culling/spatial partitioning/on-demand loading.
